A security guard beaten and wounded by robbers died at the Embu Hospital as there were no nurses to attend to him.Thirty-year-old Elias Kariuki and his 47-year-old colleague, Joel Mwaniki, who are employed by the Upcountry Guards Company and stationed at the Kettino Matatu Sacco petrol station along the Embu-Kiritiri road, were ambushed by robbers at 1am on Tuesday.Embu West subcounty police boss Francis Sang said the thugs, who were armed with crude weapons, descended on the two, injuring them critically. Sang said the robbers stole Sh120,000. The two guards were left dead. Kariuki succumbed to injuries at the hospital.